The paper deals with the calculation of hypervolume, which is a quality indicator used in multiobjective evolutionary algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses a divide and conquer scheme, which is a common technique in algorithms and data structures. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with d-dimensional spaces, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves computational study, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves optimization and efficiency, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
